<colspec colnum="2" colname="c2"/>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry>Step 1. <emphasis effect="bold">Read</emphasis> the problem. Draw the figure and label it with the given information.</entry>
<entry>The figure is provided.</entry>
</row>
 <row>
 <entry>Step 2. <emphasis effect="bold">Identify</emphasis> what you are looking for.</entry>
  <entry>The length of the sides of similar triangles</entry>
 </row>
 <row>
 <entry>Step 3. <emphasis effect="bold">Name.</emphasis> Choose a variable to represent it.</entry>
 <entry>Let<newline/><emphasis effect="italics">a</emphasis> = length of the third side of <m:math><m:mo>Δ</m:mo><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math><newline/><emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis> = length of the third side <m:math><m:mo>Δ</m:mo><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mi>Y</m:mi><m:mi>Z</m:mi></m:math></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
 <entry namest="c1" nameend="c2">Step 4. <emphasis effect="bold">Translate.</emphasis></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
 <entry namest="c1" nameend="c2">The triangles are similar, so the corresponding sides are in the same ratio. So<newline/><equation id="eip-id1168047609178" class="unnumbered"><label/><m:math><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mi>B</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mi>Y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>Y</m:mi><m:mi>Z</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mi>Z</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mfrac></m:math></equation><newline/>Since the side <m:math><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:math> corresponds to the side <m:math><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mi>Y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:math>, we will use the ratio <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mi fontstyle="italic">AB</m:mi><m:mi fontstyle="italic">XY</m:mi></m:mfrac><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> to find the other sides.<newline/><newline/>Be careful to match up corresponding sides correctly.<newline/><media id="eip-id1168466157429" alt="."><image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_09_03_057_img-01.png"/></media></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
 <entry>Step 5. <emphasis effect="bold">Solve</emphasis> the equation.</entry>
 <entry><media id="eip-id1168466188711" alt="."><image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_09_03_057_img-02.png"/></media></entry>
 </row>
 <row>
 <entry>Step 6. <emphasis effect="bold">Check:</emphasis><newline/><media id="eip-id1168469628162" alt="."><image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_09_03_057_img-03.png"/></media></entry>
 <entry/>
 </row>
 <row>
 <entry>Step 7. <emphasis effect="bold">Answer</emphasis> the question.</entry>
 <entry>The third side of <m:math><m:mo>Δ</m:mo><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:math> is 6 and the third side of <m:math><m:mo>Δ</m:mo><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mi>Y</m:mi><m:mi>Z</m:mi></m:math> is 2.4.</entry>
 </row>

